        "text": "The term “autopoiesis” was coined by Chilean biologist Humberto Maturana as part of an attempt to develop a definition of the organisation of living organisms. Maturana states that a living system is characterized by the ability of its constituent elements to produce and re-produce themselves, and in so doing to define its unity: every cell is the result of the network-internal op- erations [→[[Operation/Observation]]] of the system to which it belongs—it is not the result of any external intervention.\n"
